THE COMPOSITE HADRONS
built from quarks bound by gluons
these are the building blocks of nuclei

COMPOSITE proton
  constituents up_quark up_quark down_quark
  binding_force strong_nuclear
  binding_energy 938.3
  charge 1.0
  spin 0.5
  mass_mev 938.272
  stability stable
  magnetic_moment 2.793
  quark_sea virtual quark-antiquark pairs
  99 percent of the proton mass comes from binding energy not quark mass
  the strong force is so powerful it creates mass from pure energy
  E equals mc² made manifest

COMPOSITE neutron
  constituents up_quark down_quark down_quark
  binding_force strong_nuclear
  binding_energy 939.6
  charge 0.0
  spin 0.5
  mass_mev 939.565
  stability free_half_life 611 seconds
  inside a nucleus the neutron is stabilized by binding energy
  free neutrons decay via weak force into proton plus electron plus antineutrino
  this is beta decay
  this is the weak force changing quark flavor

COMPOSITE deuteron
  constituents proton neutron
  binding_force strong_nuclear residual
  binding_energy 2.224
  charge 1.0
  spin 1.0
  mass_mev 1875.613
  role simplest nucleus hydrogen-2
  the residual strong force that binds nucleons is mediated by pion exchange


THE ATOMS — CHNOPS
carbon hydrogen nitrogen oxygen phosphorus sulfur
these six elements constitute 98 percent of living matter
every atom in Fadriel is built from these

ATOM hydrogen
  symbol H
  atomic_number 1
  protons 1
  neutrons 0
  electrons 1
  electron_config 1s1
  electronegativity 2.20
  ionization_energy_ev 13.6
  atomic_radius_pm 53
  abundance_universe 0.75
  role universal_fuel simplest_atom
  bonds_to oxygen carbon nitrogen sulfur
  bond_types covalent ionic hydrogen
  isotopes protium deuterium tritium
  this is the most abundant element in the universe
  stellar fusion begins with hydrogen
  hydrogen bonding holds DNA together and folds proteins

ATOM carbon
  symbol C
  atomic_number 6
  protons 6
  neutrons 6
  electrons 6
  electron_config 1s2 2s2 2p2
  electronegativity 2.55
  ionization_energy_ev 11.26
  atomic_radius_pm 77
  valence 4
  hybridization sp sp2 sp3
  role backbone_of_life
  bonds_to hydrogen oxygen nitrogen sulfur carbon phosphorus
  bond_types single double triple aromatic
  this element can form 4 simultaneous covalent bonds
  this is why carbon is the skeleton of organic chemistry
  carbon's tetrahedral geometry creates 3-dimensional molecular architecture
  without carbon there is no organic chemistry no amino acids no proteins no life
  diamond is sp3 carbon graphite is sp2 carbon
  same element different orbital hybridization different material

ATOM nitrogen
  symbol N
  atomic_number 7
  protons 7
  neutrons 7
  electrons 7
  electron_config 1s2 2s2 2p3
  electronegativity 3.04
  ionization_energy_ev 14.53
  atomic_radius_pm 75
  valence 3
  role amino_acid_backbone neurotransmitter_core nucleic_acid_base
  bonds_to hydrogen carbon oxygen
  lone_pair 1
  the lone pair on nitrogen makes it a hydrogen bond acceptor
  every amino acid has an amine group NH2
  the peptide bond C-N links amino acids into proteins
  nitrogen is in the ring structure of every purine and pyrimidine
  adenine guanine cytosine thymine all contain nitrogen
  dopamine serotonin norepinephrine adrenaline all contain nitrogen

ATOM oxygen
  symbol O
  atomic_number 8
  protons 8
  neutrons 8
  electrons 8
  electron_config 1s2 2s2 2p4
  electronegativity 3.44
  ionization_energy_ev 13.62
  atomic_radius_pm 73
  valence 2
  role oxidizer universal_solvent energy_currency
  bonds_to hydrogen carbon nitrogen phosphorus sulfur
  lone_pairs 2
  the two lone pairs make oxygen a powerful hydrogen bond acceptor
  water is liquid because of oxygen's hydrogen bonding
  cellular respiration: glucose plus oxygen yields CO2 plus H2O plus ATP
  oxygen is the terminal electron acceptor in the electron transport chain
  without oxygen there is no aerobic metabolism

ATOM phosphorus
  symbol P
  atomic_number 15
  protons 15
  neutrons 16
  electrons 15
  electron_config 1s2 2s2 2p6 3s2 3p3
  electronegativity 2.19
  ionization_energy_ev 10.49
  valence 5
  role energy_storage dna_backbone signaling
  bonds_to oxygen hydrogen carbon
  the phosphodiester bond links nucleotides in DNA and RNA
  the backbone of every chromosome is sugar-phosphate
  ATP is adenosine triphosphate: three phosphate groups
  breaking one phosphate bond releases 30.5 kJ per mol
  this is the energy currency of all cellular work
  phosphorylation is how cells send signals

ATOM sulfur
  symbol S
  atomic_number 16
  protons 16
  neutrons 16
  electrons 16
  electron_config 1s2 2s2 2p6 3s2 3p4
  electronegativity 2.58
  ionization_energy_ev 10.36
  valence 2 4 6
  role disulfide_bonds protein_folding methionine cysteine
  bonds_to carbon hydrogen oxygen nitrogen
  the disulfide bond S-S links two cysteine residues
  this cross-link determines the 3D shape of proteins
  protein shape determines protein function
  a misfolded protein is a broken machine
  prions are proteins that misfold other proteins
  sulfur is in methionine the universal start codon amino acid


THE ADDITIONAL ATOMS — TRACE ELEMENTS
not CHNOPS but biologically essential

ATOM iron
  symbol Fe
  atomic_number 26
  electron_config [Ar] 3d6 4s2
  role hemoglobin oxygen_transport electron_transport
  every hemoglobin molecule has a single iron atom at its center
  iron binds oxygen reversibly in the heme group
  without iron blood cannot carry oxygen

ATOM calcium
  symbol Ca
  atomic_number 20
  role bone_structure muscle_contraction neurotransmitter_release
  calcium ions trigger vesicle fusion at synapses
  every thought Fadriel has requires calcium ions at the synapse

ATOM sodium
  symbol Na
  atomic_number 11
  role action_potential nerve_conduction fluid_balance
  sodium influx through voltage-gated channels depolarizes neurons
  the sodium-potassium pump consumes 40 percent of resting metabolic energy

ATOM potassium
  symbol K
  atomic_number 19
  role repolarization resting_potential cardiac_rhythm
  potassium efflux repolarizes neurons after firing
  the resting membrane potential of -70mV is set by potassium leak channels

ATOM chlorine
  symbol Cl
  atomic_number 17
  role inhibitory_potential GABA_receptor stomach_acid
  chloride ions flow through GABA-A receptors inhibiting neurons
  hydrochloric acid in the stomach has pH 1.5 to 3.5


THE BRIDGE MOLECULES
where quantum becomes chemistry
every chemical in 2_chemical.rana traces back to atoms defined above

MOLECULE water
  formula H2O
  atoms hydrogen 2 oxygen 1
  molecular_weight 18.015
  bond_type covalent polar
  bond_angle 104.5
  dipole_moment 1.85
  boiling_point 100
  role universal_solvent
  water is polar because oxygen pulls electrons harder than hydrogen
  the bent shape means the charge is not symmetric
  the dipole makes water the universal solvent
  60 percent of Fadriel's body mass is water

MOLECULE glucose
  formula C6H12O6
  atoms carbon 6 hydrogen 12 oxygen 6
  molecular_weight 180.16
  role primary_energy_source
  aerobic_yield 36 ATP per molecule
  glycolysis splits glucose into two pyruvate in the cytoplasm
  the citric acid cycle extracts electrons in the mitochondria
  the electron transport chain uses those electrons to pump protons
  ATP synthase converts the proton gradient into ATP
  this is how Fadriel converts food into usable energy

MOLECULE atp
  formula C10H16N5O13P3
  atoms carbon 10 hydrogen 16 nitrogen 5 oxygen 13 phosphorus 3
  molecular_weight 507.18
  role energy_currency
  hydrolysis_energy_kj -30.5
  every muscle contraction requires ATP
  every nerve impulse requires ATP
  every chemical synthesis requires ATP
  the body recycles its own weight in ATP every day

MOLECULE amino_acid_generic
  formula NH2-CHR-COOH
  role protein_building_block
  there are 20 standard amino acids
  the R group determines which one
  the peptide bond links carboxyl to amine with water released
  proteins are linear chains of amino acids folded into 3D shapes

MOLECULE dopamine
  formula C8H11NO2
  atoms carbon 8 hydrogen 11 nitrogen 1 oxygen 2
  molecular_weight 153.18
  precursor tyrosine
  synthesis_organ vta substantia_nigra
  synthesis_pathway tyrosine → tyrosine_hydroxylase → L-DOPA → dopa_decarboxylase → dopamine
  rate_limiting_enzyme tyrosine_hydroxylase
  clearance MAO-B COMT
  half_life_seconds 300
  receptors D1 D2 D3 D4 D5
  role reward wanting learning motivation
  this is the molecule of desire
  not pleasure: WANTING
  dopamine fires in anticipation not consumption

MOLECULE serotonin
  formula C10H12N2O
  atoms carbon 10 hydrogen 12 nitrogen 2 oxygen 1
  molecular_weight 176.22
  precursor tryptophan
  synthesis_organ raphe_nuclei gut_enterochromaffin
  synthesis_pathway tryptophan → tryptophan_hydroxylase → 5-HTP → AADC → serotonin
  rate_limiting_enzyme tryptophan_hydroxylase
  clearance MAO-A
  half_life_seconds 600
  receptors 5-HT1A 5-HT1B 5-HT2A 5-HT2C 5-HT3 5-HT4
  gut_fraction 0.90
  brain_fraction 0.05
  role mood_baseline contentment impulse_control satiety
  90 percent of serotonin is in the gut not the brain
  brain serotonin and gut serotonin do not cross the blood-brain barrier
  the brain must synthesize its own from tryptophan

MOLECULE norepinephrine
  formula C8H11NO3
  atoms carbon 8 hydrogen 11 nitrogen 1 oxygen 3
  molecular_weight 169.18
  precursor dopamine
  synthesis_organ locus_coeruleus adrenal_medulla
  synthesis_pathway dopamine → dopamine_beta_hydroxylase → norepinephrine
  clearance MAO COMT
  half_life_seconds 420
  receptors alpha1 alpha2 beta1 beta2
  role alertness attention threat_response vigilance
  norepinephrine is the molecule of wakefulness
  the locus coeruleus projects to every cortical region

MOLECULE adrenaline
  formula C9H13NO3
  atoms carbon 9 hydrogen 13 nitrogen 1 oxygen 3
  molecular_weight 183.20
  precursor norepinephrine
  synthesis_organ adrenal_medulla
  synthesis_pathway norepinephrine → PNMT → adrenaline
  rate_limiting_enzyme PNMT
  PNMT_requires cortisol
  clearance MAO COMT
  half_life_seconds 150
  receptors beta1 beta2 alpha1 alpha2
  role emergency_response fight_or_flight
  adrenaline is only synthesized with cortisol present
  the adrenal medulla is the only organ that makes adrenaline
  this is the molecule of emergency

MOLECULE cortisol
  formula C21H30O5
  atoms carbon 21 hydrogen 30 oxygen 5
  molecular_weight 362.46
  precursor cholesterol
  synthesis_organ adrenal_cortex
  synthesis_pathway cholesterol → pregnenolone → progesterone → 11-deoxycortisol → cortisol
  clearance 11-beta-HSD liver
  half_life_seconds 4800
  receptors glucocorticoid_receptor mineralocorticoid_receptor
  role stress_response anti_inflammatory glucose_mobilization
  cortisol suppresses the immune system
  cortisol suppresses TPH2 transcription reducing serotonin synthesis
  chronic cortisol kills hippocampal neurons
  cortisol is not the enemy: it mobilizes energy for survival
  cortisol becomes toxic only when chronic

MOLECULE oxytocin
  formula C43H66N12O12S2
  atoms carbon 43 hydrogen 66 nitrogen 12 oxygen 12 sulfur 2
  molecular_weight 1007.19
  synthesis_organ hypothalamus_paraventricular hypothalamus_supraoptic
  release_organ posterior_pituitary
  clearance oxytocinase
  half_life_seconds 14400
  receptors OXTR
  role bonding trust social_attachment lactation
  oxytocin has two disulfide bonds from sulfur
  those disulfide bonds give the molecule its shape
  shape determines function: this shape means trust
  oxytocin suppresses HPA axis reducing cortisol
  this is the molecule of love

MOLECULE gaba
  formula C4H9NO2
  atoms carbon 4 hydrogen 9 nitrogen 1 oxygen 2
  molecular_weight 103.12
  precursor glutamate
  synthesis_pathway glutamate → GAD → GABA
  rate_limiting_enzyme glutamic_acid_decarboxylase
  clearance GABA-T
  half_life_seconds 300
  receptors GABA-A GABA-B
  role inhibition calm anxiety_reduction sedation
  GABA is the primary inhibitory neurotransmitter
  GABA-A receptors are chloride channels: Cl⁻ influx hyperpolarizes the neuron
  excitation is the precursor of inhibition: glutamate becomes GABA

MOLECULE glutamate
  formula C5H9NO4
  atoms carbon 5 hydrogen 9 nitrogen 1 oxygen 4
  molecular_weight 147.13
  precursor glutamine
  synthesis_pathway glutamine → glutaminase → glutamate
  clearance glutamine_synthetase
  half_life_seconds 180
  receptors NMDA AMPA kainate
  role excitation learning memory synaptic_plasticity
  glutamate is the primary excitatory neurotransmitter
  NMDA receptors require both glutamate and depolarization
  this coincidence detection IS the mechanism of learning
  too much glutamate kills neurons: excitotoxicity

MOLECULE acetylcholine
  formula C7H16NO2
  atoms carbon 7 hydrogen 16 nitrogen 1 oxygen 2
  molecular_weight 146.21
  precursor choline
  synthesis_pathway choline → ChAT → acetylcholine
  rate_limiting_enzyme choline_acetyltransferase
  clearance acetylcholinesterase
  half_life_seconds 120
  receptors nicotinic muscarinic_M1 muscarinic_M2
  role attention memory_encoding neuromuscular_junction vagal_brake
  acetylcholine at M2 receptors slows the heart
  acetylcholine at nicotinic receptors triggers muscle contraction
  acetylcholine in the hippocampus gates memory encoding
  Alzheimer's disease destroys cholinergic neurons

MOLECULE melatonin
  formula C13H16N2O2
  atoms carbon 13 hydrogen 16 nitrogen 2 oxygen 2
  molecular_weight 232.28
  precursor serotonin
  synthesis_organ pineal_gland
  synthesis_pathway serotonin → AANAT → N-acetylserotonin → HIOMT → melatonin
  rate_limiting_enzyme AANAT
  AANAT_activated_by darkness via sympathetic_chain from SCN
  clearance CYP1A2
  half_life_seconds 2400
  receptors MT1 MT2
  role circadian_timing sleep_pressure antioxidant
  melatonin is serotonin transformed by darkness
  contentment in the light becomes rest in the dark
  same molecule different enzyme different function

MOLECULE endorphin
  formula large_peptide 31 amino acids
  molecular_weight 3465.0
  precursor POMC
  synthesis_organ anterior_pituitary hypothalamus
  synthesis_pathway POMC → prohormone_convertase → beta-endorphin + ACTH
  clearance peptidases
  half_life_seconds 10800
  receptors mu_opioid delta_opioid
  role pain_relief euphoria stress_buffering
  beta-endorphin and ACTH are cleaved from the SAME precursor POMC
  stress produces both the stress hormone and the painkiller simultaneously
  pain and its relief are inseparable at the molecular level


THE PRECURSOR CHAINS — where identity flows downhill

CHAIN catecholamine
  tyrosine → L-DOPA → dopamine → norepinephrine → adrenaline
  tyrosine_hydroxylase is the rate-limiting gate
  pleasure and emergency share the same assembly line
  the product of wanting becomes the raw material of alertness
  the product of alertness becomes the raw material of emergency

CHAIN indolamine
  tryptophan → 5-HTP → serotonin → N-acetylserotonin → melatonin
  tryptophan_hydroxylase is the rate-limiting gate
  contentment and sleep share the same assembly line
  tryptophan allocation under stress shifts to kynurenine pathway
  cortisol above 0.45 diverts tryptophan away from serotonin
  this is the direct biochemical link between chronic stress and depression

CHAIN inhibitory
  glutamine → glutamate → GABA
  excitation is the literal precursor of inhibition
  the universe builds brakes from accelerators

CHAIN stress
  cholesterol → pregnenolone → cortisol
  POMC → ACTH + beta-endorphin
  stress and pain relief emerge from the same cleavage


these particles are not metaphors
these atoms are not poetry
these molecules are not prose
they are the computable substrate
every force every bond every reaction
obeys the laws encoded in 1_quantum.rana
and interacts through the properties defined in 0_quseptit.rana

Layer 1 is not a concept
Layer 1 is physics
and now it has data
